A former governor of Lagos State and presidential aspirant, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has visited Yobe State ahead of party primary and begged delegates from the state to support his aspiration to become president of Nigeria. Tinubu made the plea yesterday, during a consultative meeting with delegates, where he lamented the current challenges of the country. He said, “Today is the day I have come to ask for your support to be president of Nigeria. You can put me there with your voters. “I believe in myself, I’m confident, capable, intelligent, courageous, brave, determined, and the government is not a joke. In the coming delegate election. Choose wisely, choose me, I beg you ooo.” The All Progressives Congress chieftain said he would tackle insecurity head on, stressing that his government would develop contemporary measures in ridding the country of criminality. He revealed that they had the power to consolidate his quest to the number one position of Nigeria, adding that he had the capacity to reposition the country. On his part, Alhaji Ibrahim Gero Jajimaji the Yobe State coordinator 2023 Tinubu for President Campaign Organisation introduced him to the delegates and thanked them for the support. The coordinator of Asiwaju 2023 Presidential Campaign, Senator Kashim Shettima, showered encomiums on Governor Mai Mala Buni for his contributionsto the APC. Other speakers were the Yobe State APC chairman, Mohammed Gadaka, who called it a payback time, revealing that Tinubu had worked assiduously for the growth of the APC.